CBRE as the exclusive sales agents are pleased to present to market 134 & 136 Crown Street, Darlinghurst. The two terraces represent an extremely rare opportunity situated in the heart of the vibrant inner-city suburb of Darlinghurst. Being offered to the market for the first time in 25 years, the characterful two storey terraces each comprise four spacious (4) bedrooms, ground and first floor veranda’s, courtyard, and rear access parking via Rosella Lane to be sold separately. Sitting on a fantastic 160sqm* and 153sqm* site area respectively, the properties are positioned in a convenient location adjacent from popular cafés and eateries, and a short walk from Oxford Street’s electrifying hub of café’s, bars, eateries, and Sydney CBD (1.1km*). 

The extremely desirable location is bolstered by its proximity to prestigious schools, universities, transport, shops, parks, and hospitals. 134 & 136 Crown Street enjoys favourable planning controls including B4 Mixed Use zoning, permitting an office or retail development with a generous potential GFA of 382.5sqm* and 400sqm*. Additionally, the property offers the opportunity to be converted into your dream home, allowing for work from home comfort in a prestige inner-city location (STCA).

134 & 136 Crown Street, Darlinghurst benefit from the following details:

•Offered to the market for the first time in 25 years
•Two characterful terraces offered separately in a desirable and tightly held inner-city location
•Each terrace comprises four (4) spacious bedrooms, ground and first floor verandas, courtyards, and rear access parking available to each property via Rosella Lane. 
•Outstanding opportunity to convert into your dream home/work from home (STCA)
•Favourable planning controls including B4 Mixed Use zoning, FSR of 2.5:1, and 15m height of building limit permitting an office or retail development (STCA)
•Potential gross floor area achievable: 400sqm* and 382.5sqm* respectively
•Internal area equating to 153sqm* and 191sqm* respectively
•Rear street access with off street parking for each terrace
•Situated in the heart of Darlinghurst and moments from its charismatic cafés, eateries, prestigious schools, transport, and Sydney CBD. 

134 & 136 Crown Street, Darlinghurst will be sold via two separate online Public Auctions at auctionWORKS on Tuesday 14 September 2021. (registration, livestream & online bidding will be available)

134 Crown Street, Darlinghurst: 10:30am
136 Crown Street, Darlinghurst: 10:45am

Inspections to be held by appointment as per COVID-19 Greater Sydney restriction requirements. Please enquire directly with the exclusive agents to arrange a private viewing.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approx

CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to offer 182 Campbell Street to market. The property is a freehold retail investment located in the burgeoning city fringe suburb of Darlinghurst. Tenanted by the popular American-themed restaurant, Surly’s, 182 Campbell Street presents a secure investment with strong growth prospects.

182 Campbell Street, Darlinghurst benefits from the following key attributes:

- Tenanted by Surly’s, a popular three storey American-themed restaurant 
- Net income: $224,081 per annum*
- 10 + 10 year lease (January 2015 lease commencement)
- Annual increases: CPI + 1%
- NLA: 471sqm* across three storeys
- Desirable city fringe location in a strong growth suburb
- Dual frontages along Campbell Street and Taggarts Lane
- Alexander & Co designed internal fit out

The property will be offered for sale via public auction at AuctionWORKS, Mezzanine Level, 50 Margaret Street, Sydney on Tuesday 24 October 2017 at 10:30am (AEST).

*Approximate

CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present to you 393 Liverpool Street, Darlinghurst. The property is a distinctive three-storey mixed use freehold building located within Sydney’s City Fringe. The property boasts a northerly aspect and features a stylish facade with polished concrete and red stainless-steel cladding. Once a popular food stall at various markets across Sydney, the ground floor is tenanted by vegan eatery, Simply Hummus Bar. Above the retail shop, the property features two whole floor residential units.

•	B4 Mixed Use zoning suitable for commercial, retail and residential
•	Strata property with ability to sell down individually in the future
•	Fully leased investment with mixed range of tenants
•	Moments from Kings Cross train & bus services, Sydney CBD, amenities, shops and restaurants

393 Liverpool Street, Darlinghurst will be sold via Public Auction on Tuesday, 7th of April 2020 at 12.00pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate
